# Skill and subagent routing

Canonical detail: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) sections **Skill and subagent routing** and **Issue registration**.

## Engineering roles (default)

| Situation | Role | Action |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Single scoped issue | Solo agent wears Dev + QA + DevOps + ship | Implement, verify, then commit/push/PR per quality gates |
| PO lists 2+ separate issues | Coordinator + work subagents + ship subagent | Scope gate → one work subagent per issue → integration verify → security review → one ship subagent |
| Parallel independent work | Work subagents (`generalPurpose`, `explore`, `shell`) | Launch concurrently when paths do not conflict; verify only, no per-subagent PRs |

## Specialized skills and subagents

| Trigger | Use | When NOT to use |
| --- | --- | --- |
| PO lists multiple separate tasks | flows-coordinator skill | Single-issue work |
| GitHub issues, PRs, checks, merge | gh-cli skill (`gh` in shell) | Pure local code edits with no GitHub action |
| Ship after verified work (solo or coordinator) | ce-commit-push-pr skill (ship subagent) | Work subagents when coordinator active; explicit PO skip signals only |
| Substantial diff before PR | ce-code-review skill or `code-reviewer` subagent | Trivial one-line fixes |
| PO asks for security review | review-security skill + `security-review` subagent (readonly) | Non-security changes |
| Diff touches security surface (see MUST triggers below) | `security-review` subagent (readonly) | MUST run after synthesis on combined diff, before ship subagent |
| Test failure or unexpected behavior | ce-debug or systematic-debugging skill | Before proposing fixes |
| Work in area covered by `docs/solutions/` | ce-learnings-researcher skill | Greenfield with no prior learning |
| PR CI failing after push | fix-ci or loop-on-ci skill | Ship subagent owns; coordinator MAY own if ship subagent cannot loop |
| PO asks Bugbot-style review | review-bugbot skill + `bugbot` subagent (readonly) | Routine self-review |

**MUST triggers for `security-review` before merge:** auth middleware; API keys or secrets handling; public unauthenticated endpoints; PII handling; payment flows; issues labeled `type:security`.

## Coordinator duties

- Scope gate: open or claim issues before delegation.
- Pick the skill or subagent type from the table; do not ask the PO to choose implementation libraries.
- Register out-of-scope findings per issue-registration rule; do not expand the current slice.
- Synthesize work subagent outputs in outcome language for the PO.
- Re-run quality gates on combined tree after synthesis.
- Run security-review when triggered, before ship subagent.
- Spawn one ship subagent after partial-ship rules pass; MUST NOT commit/push/PR directly when work subagents were spawned.
- Ship subagent (or coordinator fallback) owns loop-on-ci after push.
